## Relay-P15 Relay-P15 Segmented Token Progress Bar — Code Implementation
**Status:** draft
**Priority:** P0
**Milestone:** Relay-G17
**Module:** relay
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:relay
**Depends on:** Relay-G17 (goal), Relay-A9 (architecture), Relay-D15 (design)

# Relay-P15: Segmented Token Progress Bar — Code Implementation


## Overview

Replace the inline Cost Breakdown pie chart panel in RelayView.vue with a multi-color segmented progress bar. Each profession gets a colored segment proportional to its token consumption. Hover/focus reveals a tooltip with a horizontal bar chart. **Design D15 is fully approved and detailed — implement exactly as specified.**

## Risk & Mitigation

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Existing files may already be partially modified by prior attempts | Read each file fully before editing; verify current state against D15 expectations |
| Removing pie chart breaks other computed references | Search for `pieSlices`, `professionColors` usage across the file before deleting |
| Tooltip position clipping near viewport edges | D15 specifies `flip-below` class — implement per design |

## Phases

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P15.1 | Create `useProfessionSegments` composable | Coder | 1h | — | draft | Create `frontend/src/composables/useProfessionSegments.ts` per D15 §Composable: useProfessionSegments. Export `ProfessionSegment`, `TooltipBarEntry`, `PROFESSION_PALETTE`, and `useProfessionSegments()` returning `{ segments, totalUsed, tooltipEntries }`. Deliverable: file exists, TypeScript compiles, exports match D15 interface exactly. |
| P15.2 | Create `SegmentedProgressBar.vue` component | Coder | 2h | P15.1 | draft | Create `frontend/src/components/SegmentedProgressBar.vue` per D15 §Component: SegmentedProgressBar. Includes inline tooltip (not separate component). Props: `segments`, `totalBudget`, `totalUsed`, `warnThreshold?`, `dangerThreshold?`. Hover: 80ms show / 150ms hide debounce. Budget warning via `box-shadow` on `.segments-container`. ARIA: `role=progressbar`, `aria-valuenow`, `aria-valuemax`, `aria-label`. Keyboard: `focusin`/`focusout` mirror mouse. Deliverable: component renders segments with correct proportional widths, tooltip appears on hover with delay. |
| P15.3 | Modify `RelayView.vue` — remove pie chart, integrate segmented bar | Coder | 2h | P15.2 | draft | Modify `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue` per D15 §Integration Changes. **REMOVE:** inline Cost Breakdown panel (~lines 326–370), `pieSlices` computed, `professionColors` map, and all associated CSS (`.cost-panel`, `.cost-chart`, `.pie-*`, `.budget-bar`, `.budget-fill`). **ADD:** import `SegmentedProgressBar` and `useProfessionSegments`, wire composable to `professionTokens` from `useRelay()`, replace mono budget bar markup with `<SegmentedProgressBar :segments="segments" :total-budget="..." :total-used="totalUsed" />`. Deliverable: RelayView renders segmented bar in place of old budget bar; pie chart panel gone; no console errors. |
| P15.4 | Verify build and visual | Coder | 30m | P15.3 | draft | Run `npm run build` (or equivalent) to confirm no TypeScript or template compilation errors. Visually verify: (1) segments render with correct colors per `PROFESSION_PALETTE`, (2) tooltip shows on hover with horizontal bars and percentages, (3) budget warning glow appears at 70%/90% thresholds, (4) empty state shows placeholder text. Deliverable: clean build, no errors. |

## Files Summary

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `frontend/src/composables/useProfessionSegments.ts` | CREATE |
| `frontend/src/components/SegmentedProgressBar.vue` | CREATE |
| `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue` | MODIFY |
